🔤 Power Apps Text Functions & Definitions:
-------------------------------------------
Text() – Converts numbers, dates, and times into a text format. ━━━━━ Example: Text(Today(), "dd-mm-yyyy")

Concatenate() – Combines multiple text strings into together.  ━━━━━ Example: Concatenate("Hello ", "World")

Left() – Returns a specified number of characters from the start of a string. ━━━━━ Example: Left("PowerApps", 5) → "Power"

Right() – Returns characters from the end of a string.   ━━━━━ Example: Right("PowerApps", 4) → "Apps"

Mid() – Returns a substring from the middle of a string. ━━━━━ Example: Mid("PowerApps", 6, 4) → "Apps"

Len() – Returns the number of characters in a string.    ━━━━━  Example: Len("PowerApps") → 9

Upper() – Converts all text to uppercase. ━━━━━ Example: Upper("hello") → "HELLO"

Lower() – Converts all text to lowercase. ━━━━━ Example: Lower("HELLO") → "hello"

Trim() – Removes spaces from the beginning and end of a string. ━━━━━  Example: Trim(" Hello ") → "Hello"

Substitute() – Replaces part of a string with another string.   ━━━━━ Example: Substitute("Power Apps", " ", "") → "PowerApps"

Find() – Returns the position of a substring within a string (case-sensitive). ━━━━━ Example: Find("A", "PowerApps") → 6
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

➗ Power Apps Math Functions & Definitions:
-------------------------------------------
Sum() – Calculate the sum of numbers. ━━━━━ Example: Sum(1,2,3,4) → 10

Average() – Calculates the average of numbers. ━━━━━ Example: Average(5,10,15,20) → 5+10+15+20/5

Max() – Returns the highest value. ━━━━━ Example: Max(4,3,2,1) → 4

Min() – Returns the lowest value.  ━━━━━ Example: Min(1,2,3,4) → 1

Round() – Rounds a number to the specified decimal places. ━━━━━ Example: Round(12.345, 2) → 12.35

RoundDown() – Rounds a number down. ━━━━━ Example: RoundDown(12.9, 0) → 12

RoundUp() – Rounds a number up. ━━━━━ Example: RoundUp(12.1, 0) → 13

Mod() – Returns the remainder of a division operation. ━━━━━ Example: Mod(10, 3) → 1

Abs() – Returns the absolute (positive) value of a number. ━━━━━ Example: Abs(-5) → 5
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

📅 Power Apps Date Functions & Definitions:
-------------------------------------------
Today() – Returns the current date (without time). ━━━━━ Example: Today() → 03-05-2025

Now() – Returns the current date and time. ━━━━━ Example: Now() → 03-05-2025 11:45 AM

DateAdd() – Adds or subtracts days, months, or years to/from a date. ━━━━━ Example: DateAdd(Today(), 5) → 5 days from today

DateDiff() – Calculate the difference between two dates in days, months, or years. ━━━━━ Example: DateDiff(Today(), DatePicker1.SelectedDate)

Year() – Extracts the year from a date. ━━━━━ Example: Year(Today()) → 2025

Month() – Extracts the month from a date. ━━━━━ Example: Month(Today()) → 5

Day() – Extracts the day from a date. ━━━━━ Example: Day(Today()) → 3

Time() – Creates a time value from hours, minutes, and seconds. ━━━━━ Example: Time(10, 30, 0) → 10:30 AM

DateValue() – Converts a text string to a date. ━━━━━ Example: DateValue("03/05/2025")
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

✅ Power Apps Logical Functions & Definitions:
----------------------------------------------
If() – Checks a condition and returns different results for true/false. ━━━━━ If(Age > 18, "Adult", "Minor") 

IsBlank() – Check if a value is blank and returns true. ━━━━━ If(IsBlank(TextInput1.Text), "Required", "OK")        

IsEmpty() – Check if a collection or table has no records and returns true. ━━━━━ If(IsEmpty(MyCollection), "No Data", "Data Available")

IsNumeric() – Check if a value is Numeric and returns true. ━━━━━ IsNumeric(TextInput.text)

And() – Check if all conditions are true and returns true. ━━━━━ If(1=1 And 2=2,true,false) / If(1=1 && 2=2,true,false)
(t*f,f*t,f*f – false) || (t*t – true)

Or() – Check if any condition is true and returns true. ━━━━━ If(1=1 || 1=2,true,false) / If(1=1 Or 1=2,true,false)
(t+f,f+t,t+t – true) || (f+f – false)

Not() – Reverses the result of a condition (true becomes false). ━━━━━ If(!(1=1),true,false) / If(Not(1=2),true,false)

Coalesce() – Returns the first non-blank value from a list. ━━━━━ Coalesce(TextInput1.Text, "Default Value")























